
Subdirectories
--------------

airfoil		-- C++ version of 2D airfoil code

airfoil_F	-- original FORTRAN version of 2D airfoil code

common		-- OP2 header/library files and MATLAB generators

doc		-- LaTeX documentation

jac1		-- simple Jacobi iteration example

jac2		-- modified version which tests additional aspects


---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Contents of common
------------------

cutil_inline.h	-- stripped-down version of NVIDIA header file

op2.m		-- prototype pre-processor, written in MATLAB

op_datatypes.h	-- header used by almost all files

op_lib.cu	-- OP2 routines for CUDA execution
op_lib.cpp	-- OP2 routines for OpenMP execution

op_seq.cpp	-- routines for single-thread CPU execution

op_seq.h	-- header for single-thread CPU execution
op_seq_gen.m	-- MATLAB routine to create op_seq.h


---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Contents of doc
---------------

at.tex/pdf	 -- ideas on auto-tuning

op2.tex/pdf	 -- project notes

user.tex/pdf	 -- documentation for users

projects.tex/pdf -- possible student mini-projects

tools.tex/pdf	 -- thoughts on software tools

user.tex/pdf	 -- OP2 user guide


---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Contents of jac1
----------------

jac.cpp		  -- simple Jacobi iteration testcase

jac_kernels.cu	  -- CUDA file to include CUDA kernel files, created by op2.m
jac_kernels.cpp	  -- corresponding C++ file for OpenMP executable

jac_op.cpp	  -- main program for CUDA/OpenMP execution, created by op2.m

res.h		  -- kernel function
res_kernel.cu	  -- kernel function for CUDA execution, created by op2.m
res_kernel.cpp	  -- corresponding C++/OpenMP file, created by op2.m

update.h	  -- kernel function
update_kernel.cu  -- kernel function for CUDA execution, created by op2.m
update_kernel.cpp -- corresponding C++/OpenMP file, created by op2.m

Makefile	  -- no longer based on standard CUDA SDK template


The files produced by op2.m are generated by the MATLAB command: op2('jac')

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Contents of airfoil
-------------------

airfoil.cpp		-- simple 2D airfoil testcase

airfoil_kernels.cu	-- file to include CUDA kernel files, created by op2.m
airfoil_kernels.cpp	-- corresponding C++ file for OpenMP executable

airfoil_op.cpp		-- main program for CUDA/OpenMP execution, created by op2.m

adt_calc.h		-- kernel function
adt_calc_kernel.cu	-- kernel function for CUDA execution, created by op2.m
adt_calc_kernel.cpp	-- corresponding C++/OpenMP file, created by op2.m

bres_calc.h		-- kernel function
bres_calc_kernel.cu	-- kernel function for CUDA execution, created by op2.m
bres_calc_kernel.cpp	-- corresponding C++/OpenMP file, created by op2.m

res_calc.h		-- kernel function
res_calc_kernel.cu	-- kernel function for CUDA execution, created by op2.m
res_calc_kernel.cpp	-- corresponding C++/OpenMP file, created by op2.m

save_soln.h		-- kernel function
save_soln_kernel.cu	-- kernel function for CUDA execution, created by op2.m
save_soln_kernel.cpp	-- corresponding C++/OpenMP file, created by op2.m

update.h		-- kernel function
update_kernel.cu	-- kernel function for CUDA execution, created by op2.m
update_kernel.cpp	-- corresponding C++/OpenMP file, created by op2.m

Makefile		-- no longer based on standard CUDA SDK template


The files produced by op2.m are generated by the MATLAB command: op2('airfoil')

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

To produce tar file, do "make clean" in testcase subdirectories and then:

tar cvf op2.tar airfoil common doc jac1 README
